ws0"></div><div class="t m109 x7f hb y353 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m57a x64 hb y19 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ps. 37:38 </div><div class="t m3d x17 hb y19 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m109 x7f hb y19 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m434 x64 hb y110 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 13:28 </div><div class="t m3d x37 hb y110 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m109 x7f hb y110 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m21c x6f hb y6cd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Heb. 10:30 </div><div class="t m3d x71 hb y6cd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m109 x7f hb y6cd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m4c5 x6f hb y8c0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rev. 20:13-15 </div><div class="t m3d x4e hb y8c0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m109 x7f hb y8c0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m2e9 x6f hb y8c1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Our God </div><div class="t m643 x78 h1f y8c1 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is a God of justice; justice may seem delayed, at least to </div><div class="t m6ae x8 h1f y8c2 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">us, but that&apos;s only because we are so limited in our understanding of </div><div class="t m70e x8 h1f y8c3 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">how God is working through all the issues in the great controversy. </div><div class="t m3a7 x8 h1f y8c4 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">For now, though there is much we don&apos;t understand, we need to daily </div><div class="t m26 x8 h1f y8c5 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">surrender ourselves to the Lord, who has given us so many reasons to </div><div class="t m60a x8 h1f y8c6 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trust Him in the things that now appear so hard to comprehend. No </div><div class="t m6e7 x8 h1f y8c7 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">doubt, too, the more we dwell on what we do understand, the more we </div><div class="t m354 x8 h1f y8c8 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">concentrate on what is clear, we will better be able to endure and trust </div><div class="t m197 x8 h1f y8c9 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Him in the things that, for the moment, seem so unfair and unjust. </div><div class="t m4e2 x73 hb y8ca ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Hector&apos;s family had suffered great persecution for their faith. </div><div class="t m136 x61 hb y8cb ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Often he thought about revenge. Only after he, himself, made a </div><div class="t m4a0 x61 hb y8cc ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">total surrender to Christ did those feelings start to dissipate. In </div><div class="t m589 x61 hb y8cd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fact, over time, he even found himself starting to pray for those </div><div class="t m70f x61 hb y8ce ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">who had treated his family so badly, even praying that they </div><div class="t m470 x61 hb y8cf ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">would be spared the judgment that God would eventually bring </div><div class="t m2d x61 hb y8d0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">upon them because of their sins. Why must we learn to leave the </div><div class="t m1f5 x61 hb y8d1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">final judgment to God? </div><div class="t mad x7b h1f y311 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">98 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
